WizardBasicStep.name: WizardBasicStep
WizardBasicStep.description: Type used to define 'basic' steps, or in other words, steps that are neither parents or children of parents.

WizardParentStep.name: WizardParentStep
WizardParentStep.description: Type used to define parent steps.

WizardStepType.name: WizardStepType
WizardStepType.description: Encompasses all step type variants that are internally controlled by the Wizard.

CustomWizardNavFunction.name: CustomWizardNavFunction
CustomWizardNavFunction.description: Callback for the Wizard's 'nav' property. Returns element which replaces the Wizard's default navigation.

CustomWizardNavItemFunction.name: CustomWizardNavItemFunction
CustomWizardNavItemFunction.description: Callback for the Wizard's 'navItem' property. Returns element which replaces the WizardStep's default navigation item.

CustomWizardFooterFunction.name: CustomWizardFooterFunction
CustomWizardFooterFunction.description: Callback for the Wizard's 'footer' property. Returns element which replaces the Wizard's default footer.

WizardToggle.name: WizardToggle
WizardToggle.description: Used to toggle between step content, including the body and footer. This is also where the navigation and its expandability is controlled.

WizardStep.name: WizardStep
WizardStep.description: The primary child component for Wizard. Step props are used for the list of steps managed in context.

WizardNavInternal.name: WizardNavInternal
WizardNavInternal.description:
Hosts default wizard navigation logic by utilizing the wizard's context and WizardNav/WizardNavItem.
This component is not exposed to consumers.

WizardBody.name: WizardBody
WizardBody.description: Used as a wrapper for WizardStep content, where the wrapping element is customizable.

Wizard.name: Wizard
Wizard.description:
Wrapper for all steps and hosts state, including navigation helpers, within context.
The WizardContext provided by default gives any child of wizard access to those resources.

TreeViewSearch.name: TreeViewSearch
TreeViewSearch.description:
Renders a search input for the tree view. This sub-component should be passed into the
tree view component's toolbar property.

TreeViewDataItem.name: TreeViewDataItem
TreeViewDataItem.description:
Properties that make up a tree view data item. These properties should be passed in as an
object to one of the various tree view component properties which accept TreeViewDataItem as
a type.

SliderStepObject.name: SliderStepObject
SliderStepObject.description:
Properties for creating custom steps in a slider. These properties should be passed in as
an object within an array to the slider component's customSteps property.

SearchInputSearchAttribute.name: SearchInputSearchAttribute
SearchInputSearchAttribute.description:
Properties for adding search attributes to an advanced search input. These properties must
be passed in as an object within an array to the search input component's attribute property.

SearchInputExpandable.name: SearchInputExpandable
SearchInputExpandable.description:
Properties for creating an expandable search input. These properties should be passed into
the search input component's expandableInput property.

SelectOption.name: SelectOption
SelectOption.description: See the MenuItem section of the Menu documentation for additional props that may be passed.

SelectGroup.name: SelectGroup
SelectGroup.description: See the MenuGroup section of the Menu documentation for additional props that may be passed.

Select.name: Select
Select.description: See the Menu documentation for additional props that may be passed.

Popover.name: Popover
Popover.description:
The main popover component. The following properties can also be passed into another component
that has a property specifically for passing in popover properties.

PerPageOptions.name: PerPageOptions
PerPageOptions.description:
Properties to customize the content and behavior of the pagination dropdown options. These
properties should be passed into the pagination component's perPageOptions property.

PaginationTitles.name: PaginationTitles
PaginationTitles.description:
Properties to customize various pagination titles. The following properties should be
passed into the pagination component's title property.

MultipleFileUploadStatusItem.name: MultipleFileUploadStatusItem
MultipleFileUploadStatusItem.description:
Automatically reads an uploaded file to render a visual representation of it, including
its name, size, and read status. This sub-component also allows custom reading of files
via various callbacks which will override the automatic reading behavior.

MultipleFileUploadStatus.name: MultipleFileUploadStatus
MultipleFileUploadStatus.description:
Acts as an expandable container for all uploaded file statuses.
An optional text and/or icon can also be passed into this sub-component.
This sub-component can be conditionally rendered when at least 1 file has been
attempted to be uploaded.

MultipleFileUploadMain.name: MultipleFileUploadMain
MultipleFileUploadMain.description:
Creates the visual upload interface, including the area to drag and drop files,
an optional upload button, and descriptive instructions.

MultipleFileUpload.name: MultipleFileUpload
MultipleFileUpload.description:
Acts as a container for all other MultipleFileUpload sub-components. This sub-component
also provides the functionality for file uploads, and access to the uploaded files via
a callback.

MenuContainer.name: MenuContainer
MenuContainer.description: Container that links a menu and menu toggle together, to handle basic keyboard input and control the opening and closing of a menu.

ModalHeader.name: ModalHeader
ModalHeader.description: Renders content in the header of the modal

ModalFooter.name: ModalFooter
ModalFooter.description: Renders content in the footer of the modal

ModalBody.name: ModalBody
ModalBody.description: Renders content in the body of the modal

FileUploadHelperText.name: FileUploadHelperText
FileUploadHelperText.description:
A container for helper text content. This sub-component should be passed as a child to
the main file upload or file upload field component.

FileUploadField.name: FileUploadField
FileUploadField.description:
A more customizable file upload component for implementing custom logic. Drag and drop
functionality is not built in by default.

ExpandableSectionToggle.name: ExpandableSectionToggle
ExpandableSectionToggle.description:
Acts as the toggle sub-component when the main expandable section component has the isDetached
property passed in. Allows for more custom control over the expandable section's toggle.

FormGroupLabelHelp.name: FormGroupLabelHelp
FormGroupLabelHelp.description:
A help button to be passed to the FormGroup's labelHelp property. This should be wrapped or linked
to our Popover component.

DualListSelectorTree.name: DualListSelectorTree
DualListSelectorTree.description:
Used in place of the DualListSelectorListItem sub-component when building a
composable dual list selector with a tree.

DualListSelectorPane.name: DualListSelectorPane
DualListSelectorPane.description:
Acts as the container for a list of options that are either available or chosen,
depending on the pane type (available or chosen). A search input and other actions,
such as sorting, can also be passed into this sub-component.

DualListSelector.name: DualListSelector
DualListSelector.description:
Acts as a container for all other DualListSelector sub-components when using a
composable dual list selector.

DropdownItem.name: DropdownItem
DropdownItem.description: See the MenuItem section of the Menu documentation for additional props that may be passed.

DropdownGroup.name: DropdownGroup
DropdownGroup.description: See the MenuGroup section of the Menu documentation for additional props that may be passed.

Dropdown.name: Dropdown
Dropdown.description: See the Menu documentation for additional props that may be passed.

DrawerPanelDescription.name: DrawerPanelDescription
DrawerPanelDescription.description: Provides a description within the drawer panel. This should typically follow the drawer head.

DatePickerRequiredObject.name: DatePickerRequiredObject
DatePickerRequiredObject.description: Props that customize the requirement of a date

DatePickerRef.name: DatePickerRef
DatePickerRef.description:
Allows finer control over the calendar's open state when a React ref is passed into the
date picker component. Accessed via ref.current[property], e.g. ref.current.toggleCalendar().

CalendarFormat.name: CalendarFormat
CalendarFormat.description:
Additional properties that extend from and can be passed to the main component. These
properties allow customizing the calendar formatting and aria-labels.

AlertActionLink.name: AlertActionLink
AlertActionLink.description:
Renders buttons styled as links beneath the alert title and description when this sub-component
is passed into the alert's actionLinks property.

AlertActionCloseButton.name: AlertActionCloseButton
AlertActionCloseButton.description:
Renders a close button for a dismissable alert when this sub-component is passed into
the alert's actionClose property.

DualListSelectorTree-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorTree-deprecated
DualListSelectorTree-deprecated.description:
Used in place of the DualListSelectorListItem sub-component when building a
composable dual list selector with a tree.

DualListSelectorTreeProps-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorTreeProps-deprecated
DualListSelectorTreeProps-deprecated.description:
Used in place of the DualListSelectorListItem sub-component when building a
composable dual list selector with a tree.

DualListSelectorPane-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorPane-deprecated
DualListSelectorPane-deprecated.description:
Acts as the container for a list of options that are either available or chosen,
depending on the pane type (available or chosen). A search input and other actions,
such as sorting, can also be passed into this sub-component.

DualListSelectorPaneProps-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorPaneProps-deprecated
DualListSelectorPaneProps-deprecated.description:
Acts as the container for a list of options that are either available or chosen,
depending on the pane type (available or chosen). A search input and other actions,
such as sorting, can also be passed into this sub-component.

DualListSelectorListItemProps-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorListItemProps-deprecated
DualListSelectorListItemProps-deprecated.description:
Creates an individual option that can be selected and moved between the
dual list selector panes. This is contained within the DualListSelectorList sub-component.

DualListSelectorList-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorList-deprecated
DualListSelectorList-deprecated.description: Acts as the container for DualListSelectorListItem sub-components.

DualListSelectorListProps-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorListProps-deprecated
DualListSelectorListProps-deprecated.description: Acts as the container for DualListSelectorListItem sub-components.

DualListSelectorControlsWrapperProps-dep.name: DualListSelectorControlsWrapperProps-deprecated
DualListSelectorControlsWrapperProps-dep.description: Acts as the container for the DualListSelectorControl sub-components.

DualListSelectorControlProps-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorControlProps-deprecated
DualListSelectorControlProps-deprecated.description:
Renders an individual control button for moving selected options between each
dual list selector pane.

DualListSelector-deprecated.name: DualListSelector-deprecated
DualListSelector-deprecated.description:
Acts as a container for all other DualListSelector sub-components when using a
composable dual list selector.

DualListSelectorProps-deprecated.name: DualListSelectorProps-deprecated
DualListSelectorProps-deprecated.description:
Acts as a container for all other DualListSelector sub-components when using a
composable dual list selector.
